   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Masrik Solar</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project&apos;s development impact includes: (i) Reduction of GHG emissions, by increasing the share of electricity supply from renewable sources, (ii) Improving energy security and lowering generation costs, by reducing the country&apos;s reliance on imported fuels for power generation, and (iii) Further strengthening competitiveness of the sector, by supporting the development of the first competitively tendered utility-scale solar IPP in the country.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed investment involves a senior loan of up to US$11 million to FRV Masrik CJSC. It will be used to finance the development, construction, operation and maintenance of a 55MWac/62MWp solar photovoltaic (PV) plant located in the municipality of Mets Masrik, Armenia. The PV plant will be connected to the national grid through a 9.2km 110kV high voltage overhead transmission line also financed as part of the Project. The Project is expected to be commissioned in 2021 and will sell electricity based on a 20-year tariff Power Purchase Agreement entered into with the private offtaker, Electric Networks of Armenia.</narrative>
  </description>
